  "texts": [
    "We also add three prompting baselines (Promptkeywords, Prompt-Mpi, and Prompt-LLM-Description) with descriptions of bigfive personality traits.",
    "As the Table 12 shows, all three prompt types seem to yield strong performance on the BFI and IPIP-NEO questionnaires, outperforming the baseline prompt-inst and approaching the performance of our training-based methods.",
    "However, upon closer examination, we found that these prompts contain many keywords that significantly overlap with the BFI and IPIP-NEO inventories.",
    "This overlap introduces the risk of circularity in evaluation, as the prompts themselves echo the structure and language of the evaluation metrics.",
    "Given that BFI and IPIP-NEO remain the standard benchmarks for assessing LLM personality, we believe the Prompt-Demo and Prompt-Inst methods, which avoids such circularity, is more suitable for fair comparison with training-based approaches."
  ],
